content: The replays! I love to watch the replays. To see the car flying at flight level zero taking the curves like a jet fighter. And look for the car's physics! The car suspension! I'm addicted to this game. As well as my sisters. Illusion Magic Studio is so cool ğŸ˜˜â¤ PS: The 3D effect is so cool! You don't just play the game, it's as if you were really IN it! And that without 3D glasses! Wow! âœŒğŸ˜ PPS: There is a potential racetrack that never got opened until now. The Coastal Highway, through the off cordoned tunnel and over a Highway, road, whatever, around upwards and on the upper level out through where it is also now cordoned off. And backwards the other direction. I wonder HOW many gamers would just wait for THAT update? ğŸ˜‰ğŸ‘

That game is not just about rally driving, but about the art of surfing the roads using your car as a surfboard. If you've developed the proper skills in perfectly driving these cars, then it's not about driving anymore but about the beauty of sliding around every curve without ever using the break. You'll be the winner if you develop the skill of taking each curve with a lead-foot on the accelerator. And after a while it even isn't anymore about winning, but only more about the pure meditative beauty of relaxation while sliding or floating all around the racetrack. To win you'll have to use the car like in reality only the best stunt-drivers are capable of. You'll get addicted to that game

content: I'm in a love/hate relationship with this game, and therefore always changing my review (sorry devs :P.) This is most likely because I'm so picky about everything. For example: the controls are bad with touchscreen, but work beautifully with a controller. Also, the game modes should vary more than Quick Race and Challenge Mode. Yes they are fun, but the Challenge I has uneccesarily long races (6+ minutes in some cases.) However, this game is definitely worth the money: beautiful graphics, accurate car models, beautiful tracks, and you can play for hours on end without your device heating up, as it does with other games. Pros/Cons balance out in this game, and I still enjoy it despite its flaws.  Other notable things about this game are: beautiful camera angles and physics that change according to drivetrain.

content: Pocket rally is a game which is definitely not easy, if you play it for the first time. You need to exercise on and on again, to get the skills you need to become successful in this game. But once you have the necessary skills, it is a wonderful feeling to just drive, on and on, forgetting about time and everything around. It is so relaxing to drive and maybe reconsider the day, in the evening, while playing the game. And just relax while driving. This game will never get boring. When you're young now, there's a really big probability that, once you are old, you will still play it. Maybe not as often as in your young days, but always again. If it's to me, I definitely will.

content: It's really good and most importantly has gamepad support unlike Colin McRae rally. Gameplay is good and a lot of fun. Graphics are good. It has well known licensed cars with great variety (Toyota Celica gt4, subaru wrx, rally raid truck, lancia stratos, and a group B Peugeot 205 t16).   Also has decent camera views. Sadly no cockpit view but it does have good hood and Chase cams plus an overhead camera that surprisingly functions well (think motorstorm RC).   Has a career mode and a few tracks. Seems like a great game for $1 and personally I think it's much for fun to play than Colin McRae rally even with touch controls, let alone gamepad which is totally superior. Frankly it's ridiculous for a game like this to not have gamepad support, especially Colin McRae rally

Minor beef: I use the tilt steering mode, but it still seems like the turning comes in increments instead of relating smoothly to how much I tilt the phone. content: I have been an avid fan of racing games since Pole Position, which a lot of kids won't even know what tha is. Lets just say - you had to stand up to play it. In the paid version you still have to unlock the cars/tracks by completing the challenges in Challenge mode. The differences between lite version and paid version:
* The lite version contains only the first 6 levels of Challenge mode, and there's in-game advertisement.
* The paid version contains all 30 levels, and is advertisement free.

I'm a rally racing fan coming from the Colin Mcrae Rally series of racing games and I must say that I'm pretty impressed with this game.  The handling of each car has a relatively realistic feel and unique handling, as a result, each car requires you to adjust your driving style.  The textures and of each course and car as well as detail put into each are somewhere between the PS1 and PS2 level of detail.  If I could list any cons, it would be brakes and application of power on each car.  The tires used on each car seem a bit too grippy.  On top of that, the brakes on each seem to be lacking, in fact, on hairpin turns in the Ancient city course, throwing the car into a slide slows the car down more effectively than applying threshold braking (straight-line braking), which is not true to life.  In future updates, I would hope to have access to car upgrades and a more realistic braking system.  Perhaps you could incorporate a sliding bar, very similar to the one used for the steering input system (I am not very fond of the tilt system and do not own an xperia controller) to control gas and braking a little more precisely.  Other than that, this is a fantastic mobile game!

Great job! I would like to see it powered as the hits like.... Less of content than them but when it comes to enjoy is even better from some. +1 and wish to see brands like....

Good graphics, physics of driving  Could use some sensitivity control adjustable, slightly better textures.  Overall fun and good game for the money.  I would add sadly seems to be the only rally racing game of substance.

This is the first game I ever bought on play because I thought there would be more maps to unlock, but now they are just the reversed way for the first two maps?! But I really like this game so please add more, and please add dust particles on the opponents too. Thanks!

Took about 2 weeks to complete challenge mode but really enjoyed it. I think the difficulty level is good, the final challenge I thought I'd never catch the Lancia but you find new places to gain extra seconds, took lots of efforts to do it though. Well done developers, when are you going to open the tunnel in coast track?

Warning !! This is not a game, its a simulator!! It has all the technicalities: jumps, off camber corners, diminishing radius curves, hairpins,dips, gravel/dirt/tarmac etc...., of rallying. Use this to practice for real-life rallying. A navigator will give it 6 stars. I have upgraded.
This has to be one of the best games I've ever played on a mobile device.  Reminds me of Top Gear Rally for the N64.
I've tried and tried to pass one track but I cannot pass it . also its 3 times around the track
By far the best game period! I'm so addicted to this game. Its a must have! I wish for a sprint car game by the same developer's! Please!! :)

Despite costing barely a dollar the game physics, bearing in mind it's a phone, are amazing. I really did not expect to find a racing game which would be that good. All the others I have tried (some costing three times as much) come nowhere close to this one.  The progression through levels is well done. It allows you to really get the hang of the tracks and cars.   The only downside is that if you start with "Pocket Rally Lite", after level 6 it will ask you to buy the full game in order to continue - but when you do get the full version, you have to start all over again. BUT having said that, it is too enjoyable to get annoyed about having to race the same cars/tracks again.  Enough said, go and play it.   The only thing I would like to see (if possible) would be multiplayer/online option. I think that would really improve it.
Challenging game
I always like the bug on the bumper or cockpit view. I think overhead view racers bite. This is a great game for Â¢99.
Great one..
I love this so much!

I understand that it's a tricky feat to strike a balance between making the game to hard and too easy. This game (at challenge 9/30) becomes pretty close to impossible. How many perfect runs do I have to race before I beat the clock? I can't play anymore, uninstall.

Looks decent and is a nice quick game but the handling seems broken, like steering a shopping trolley on an ice rink. If it could handle like the original PS1 Colin McRae or Sega Rally then it would be 5 stars easily. Also the time trials could do with being a bit more lenient, having to repeat events makes the lack of tracks seem more repetetive. Otherwise it is fun, looking forward to improvements because the game is certainly worth persevering with.
Saw this for 69p and tried the demo. One race and I instantly bought the full game. Hi-res gfx and power sliding. It's like having sega rally on my S2! Love it!!!
Gr8 game! Kudos to the team!
Love clean and sharp visual. Control can be more responsive, and please add dificulties setting. Game suppose to be fun, not frustating. :)
Really enjoying the game, great handling. Would be nice if lap times were saved and the addition of an Escort Cosworth would be cool :-)
Horrible controls

Reminds me of the old Sega rally at arcades. This game is brilliant! Can't wait to get the lancia and the escort. It is a bit hard at the start of the game,would be better if it had difficulty settings for beginners. But once you get the hang of it, you won't be able to put your phone down :)
This game is great the physics engine is amazing. But it should have a menu that allows you to pause quit and restart the game guys. Then it would be 5 stars.
replyContent: Hello, you can use the "Back" button of the phone to pause the game and bring up the quit/restart menu.

content: Excellent
I'm half way through and enjoying the game a lot. Looking forward to future updates.

This is a really good looking game but the driving is a little too unforgiving, especially in time trails. I want to pick up and just play a little on my phone, not have to practice, practice, practice just to unlock all the options. Good start. Fantastic value for money.
You rock! Finally, rally action on Android! Please, continue development.
Reminds me of Colin McRae rally on the ps1. Excellent physics and the slider control method is perfect

I would like a refund game doesn't work just black screen
replyContent: Please e-mail your order number to: wueric2003@gmail.com for refund.

Now waiting for more cars and tracks, will also be good to see particle effects such as mud and dust kicking up and maybe sticking to the cars.   One extra star added for the work so far.

One of the fun game I"v ever played

Fun game, surprisingly good gameplay. Some of the races are a bit cat and mouse which makes for an entertaining race.   I'd welcome some extra cars and more tracks to make it the complete package. For its current price its well worth buying, even just to pass some time on the bus.

This game is awesome so far and the developers have done a great job!! The sound could use some work, but the arcade'y handling is great fun. The only thing lacking is a sense of speed. It feels like the cars aren't travelling fast enough for the speeds being reported. Perhaps a Field-of-View adjustment when at higher speeds?..... or even just some motion blur. Otherwise great game!

Great little sim, good graphics, very smooth and you can feel differences in the vehicles. As far as I'm aware though, the Celica GT-Four didn't have a CVT that topped out at 60km/h... The interface could do with a little polish too.  Well worth a punt though, especially if it gets updated with new tracks/cars. Keep it up!

I have been waiting for a decent looking rally game and this is it!!! Graphics are pretty good and the car handles well in corners. Touch controls are very responsive.  Not tried tilt yet.  Track sounds like gravel and road are good but the car engine has the same pitch and constantly sounds like its in high revs. Which makes it seem really dull. Also the speedo only 70kph top speed for a high performance rally car ? That's like 40mph :/  On straights the car is too slow. On corners its fine.   Seems like a lot of races.  For 60pence its a good game but it needs improvement.

If only Sega would give us a Sega Rally port.... This will do for now though! Fun racer.

This game certainly has the potential to be good. I would agree with some of the other reviews in that it's ridiculous that you can only do 60 kmh but I suspect this is more to do with the frame rate than anything else, increase the speed and it will of course effect the draw rate and the graphics quality which I think the developer is well aware of but will work on for future updates. So don't dismiss this because it definitely has the beginnings of a good rally game which is missing from Android at mo!

This game plays really well on my experia j. Its got great graphics, and plenty of choice for controls and camera angles. This is a very well made game, I will be following the developer. Only problem is the cars dont feel very fast, if this can be adressed this would definately be a 5 star game. Great work though

If this game had 10 or so more tracks, and 10 or so more cars, native gamepad support (a must), and higher speeds (another must), I would gladly pay 5-10$ for it. Please expand on what you have here. The graphics are good enough for a phone, the cars handle brilliantly, there just isnt enough content. It is however great, just please add more and you have a fan for life here, and I promise this will be one of the best games on the store with some effort. There is money to be made for you. Thanks.
replyContent: Thank you very much, and we intend to do just that. We are planning on several improvements and add-ons for the game, and more cars and tracks off course. Give us some time!
